Next, referring to the projected future cash flows from the table in the previous step, calculate the present value of each cash flow per year.

Let's calculate the present value for the first year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV}_{1} &=\dfrac{\$1,375,000}{\left(1 + 0.065\right)^{1}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$1,375,000}{1.065}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$1,291,080 }
\end{aligned}$$

As can be seen above, the present value of lottery winning for the first year is $1,291,080.

Next, let's calculate the present value for the second year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV}_{2} &=\dfrac{\$ 1,750,000}{\left(1 + 0.065\right)^{2}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$1,750,000}{1.134225}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$1,542,904}
\end{aligned}$$

Hence, the present value for the second year is $1,542,904.

Next, let's calculate the present value for the third year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV}_{3} &=\dfrac{\$ 2,125,000}{\left(1 + 0.065\right)^{3}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$ 2,125,000 
}{1.207949625}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$1,759,179}
\end{aligned}$$


Based on our calculation, the present value of the winning for the third year is $1,759,179.

Next, let's calculate the present value for the fourth year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV}_{4} &=\dfrac{\$ 2,500,000}{\left(1 + 0.065\right)^{4}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$ 2,500,000 
}{1.286466351}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$1,943,308}
\end{aligned}$$


Hence, $1,943,308 is the present value of the lottery winning for the fourth year.

Next, let's calculate the present value for the fifth year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV}_{5} &=\dfrac{\$2,875,000}{\left(1 + 0.065\right)^{5}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$ 2,875,000}{1.370086663}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$2,098,407}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore, the present value for the fifth year is $2,098,407.

Next, let's calculate the present value for the sixth year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV}_{6} &=\dfrac{\$ 3,250,000}{\left(1 + 0.065\right)^{6}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$ 3,250,000 }{1.459142297}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$2,227,336}
\end{aligned}$$


As can be seen above, the present value for the sixth year is $2,227,336.

Next, let's calculate the present value for the seventh year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV}_{7} &=\dfrac{\$3,625,000}{\left(1 + 0.065\right)^{7}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$3,625,000}{1.553986546}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$2,332,710}
\end{aligned}$$

Hence, the present value for the seventh year is $2,332,710.

Next, let's calculate the present value for the eight-year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV}_{8} &=\dfrac{\$ 4,000,000 }{\left(1 + 0.065\right)^{8}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$ 4,000,000}{1.654995671}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$2,416,925}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore, $2,416,925 is the present value for the eighth year.

Next, let's calculate the present value for the ninth year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV}_{9} &=\dfrac{\$4,375,000}{\left(1 + 0.065\right)^{9}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$4,375,000 }{1.76257039}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$2,482,170}
\end{aligned}$$

As can be seen above, the present value for the ninth year of the lottery winning is $2,482,170.

Last, let's calculate the present value for the tenth year.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{PV}_{10} &=\dfrac{\$ 4,750,000}{\left(1 + 0.065\right)^{10}}
\\[10pt]
&=\dfrac{\$ 4,750,000 }{1.877137465}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\bf\$ 2,530,449}
\end{aligned}$$


Based on our calculation, the present value for the tenth year is $2,530,449.
